ibed, and understood sexual desire has changed dramatically over time and across cultures. This collection brings together a group of leading scholars from a variety of disciplines to explore the history of sexual desires and the transformation of sexual ideas, attitudes, and practices in premodern Europe. Among the topics considered are the visibility of sexual offenses and the construction of passions; the geographical range extends to Great Britain, with a focus also on France and Germany. The result is a groundbreaking volume that adds significantly to our understanding of premodern European history, history of sexualities, gender studies, religious history, and many other fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aSexzEuropexHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aKaartinen, Marjo, eeditor.1 aLidman, Satu, eeditor.1 aLinkinen, Tom, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2017z978311066284908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060644740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048529001zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048529001.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7  Amsterdam University Press  eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  AUP eBook Package 2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG